	<h1>Get started</h1>

	<h2>1. Installation</h2>

	<pre><code class="javascript">npm install amoeba.io</code></pre>

	<h2>2. Configure</h2>
	<p>Configuration occurs via "add" method</p>
	<pre><code class="javascript">amoeba.add([route,] object [,callback])</code></pre>
	<p>route - path refers to an object</p>
	<p>object - can be both client and server. If route params exists (string) it will be client otherwise server</p>
	<p>callback - function that will be called when server or client is ready for use or error happens</p>
	<p>Example:</p>
	<pre><code class="javascript">amoeba.add("chat", new LocalService(new Chat()), function(err){
	if(!err){
		//Client ready
		amoeba.add(new SocketServer("8081"), function(err){
			if(!err){
				//Server ready
			}
		});
	}
});</code></pre>

