	<h3>Masks</h3>
	<p>You can use mask when call use method in Amoeba. For example if you add your service next way</p>
	<pre><code class="javascript">amoeba.add("chat.*", new LocalService(new Chat()))</code></pre>
	all "invoke" calls start with "chat." will be routed to chat local service
	<pre><code class="javascript">amoeba.use("chat.room.6").invoke("add", {message: "Hello world"})</code></pre>
	You can not call "invoke" using mask
	<pre><code class="javascript">amoeba.use("chat.*").invoke("add", {message: "Hello world"}); //ERROR HERE</code></pre>
	But you can call "on" using mask
	<pre><code class="javascript">amoeba.use("chat.*").on("add", function(event, data){});
//THE SAME AS
amoeba.on("add:chat.*", function(event, data){});</code></pre>
	<p>It means that all "add" events in all services started with "chat" will call your function. </p>
	<pre><code class="javascript">chat
chat.rooms
chat.rooms.1
chat.rooms.2
chat.very.long.path
chat.etc
</code></pre>
	<p class="text-danger">Event name can use period "." but can`t colon ":"</p>


